So what's it like being back in school?

48:06.512 --> 48:09.056
I don't know. I kinda feel
like an idiot sometimes.

48:09.223 --> 48:12.309
Although I am an idiot,
so it kinda works out.

48:13.352 --> 48:16.772
Is it just you and your dad in here?

48:16.897 --> 48:21.693
Well, actually, no. There's Juanita,
and some maids and butlers and stuff.

48:21.819 --> 48:24.947
And people who work for my dad
are always stoppin' by.

48:25.072 --> 48:29.493
And my friends are always sleepin' over,
even when I didn't ask 'em to.

48:29.618 --> 48:32.704
- Sounds like a hotel.
- It kinda is. It can be distracting.

48:32.871 --> 48:35.332
That's why I moved out here.

48:47.177 --> 48:49.137
Wow.

48:49.263 --> 48:52.266
This is where I've been spending
most of my time lately.

48:52.432 --> 48:54.893
Not exactly roughing it, are you?

49:00.274 --> 49:03.777
Those are, uh...
They come with the tent, so...

49:09.324 --> 49:13.495
Oh, wow. A Tale of Two Cities.
I don't think we're up to that one yet.

49:13.620 --> 49:17.124
I can understand nine words
in that book now.

49:20.335 --> 49:24.256
So, it's, um... the last day of third grade.

49:25.299 --> 49:29.219
And you have the teacher,
alone, in your tent.

49:30.137 --> 49:32.598
What do you wanna do?

49:33.432 --> 49:37.811
Well, I can think of three things
I'd like to do.

49:37.936 --> 49:42.232
One would involve some ice cubes
and a nine-iron.

49:43.650 --> 49:46.820
- Two would include a buffalo.
- Really?

49:46.987 --> 49:52.326
Live or stuffed.
Preferably stuffed, for safety's sake.

49:52.451 --> 49:55.454
Three: we'd bring back
some of those ice cubes,...

49:55.621 --> 49:58.707
..but switch it over to a pitching wedge.

49:59.500 --> 50:01.960
How you guys doin'?

50:03.420 --> 50:07.090
Hey! Carl! Good to see you!

50:09.927 --> 50:12.471
This is Veronica, my teacher. That's Carl.

50:12.638 --> 50:16.391
Very pleased to meet you.
Bill, I think Eric is up to something.

50:16.558 --> 50:19.311
- Who's Eric?
- He works for my dad too.

50:19.436 --> 50:22.356
He gets the company if I screw up.
He's a douchebag.

50:22.523 --> 50:26.985
He made some menacing comments to me,
and then he did that little weasel laugh.

50:27.152 --> 50:31.281
- Yeah. How does that laugh go again?
- You know. (laughs )

50:32.032 --> 50:34.868
- Very good. It sounded just like him.
- Thanks.

50:34.993 --> 50:37.996
Well, I'm sure he's got
something up his sleeve.

50:38.121 --> 50:39.748
- Thanks, buddy.
- No problem.

50:40.499 --> 50:42.376
(~ 'ABC' by the Jackson 5)

50:44.628 --> 50:46.755
~ You went to school to learn, girl

50:46.880 --> 50:49.800
~ Things you never, never knew before...

50:50.884 --> 50:54.847
(teacher ) The most densely populated part
of the US is along the eastern seaboard.

50:55.013 --> 50:59.142
We're gonna talk about why that is
over the next few minutes.

50:59.309 --> 51:03.522
We all know what a census is, don't we?
That's like taking a census...

51:07.276 --> 51:09.987
You know, yeah. Pick it up and gimme...

51:10.112 --> 51:12.072
You want some of this?

51:12.239 --> 51:14.700
Oh, my dear Lord!

51:14.825 --> 51:18.412
You never leave me open, son,
cos I'm gonna hit it every time.

51:18.537 --> 51:21.290
You want some more of that?
I didn't think so!

51:22.332 --> 51:26.461
~ Reading, writing, arithmetic
are the branches of the learning tree

51:26.628 --> 51:29.882
~ But without the roots
of love every day, girl

51:30.007 --> 51:32.384
~ Your education ain't complete

51:32.509 --> 51:34.887
~ Teacher's gonna show you

51:35.053 --> 51:37.014
~ How to get an A

51:37.139 --> 51:40.142
~ How to spell 'me', 'you'
and add the two

51:40.309 --> 51:42.603
~ Listen to me, baby,
that's all you gotta do

51:42.769 --> 51:44.229
~ ABC

51:44.396 --> 51:46.773
~ It's easy as 1-2-3

51:47.024 --> 51:50.444
~ As simple as do-re-mi, ABC...

52:19.640 --> 52:22.392
(belches the alphabet )

52:26.605 --> 52:28.982
All right, stop before I throw up.

52:29.149 --> 52:32.486
Hey, Billy, you wanna go
play soccer with us after school?

52:32.611 --> 52:35.864
No, I got a test on Friday.
I'll play with you guys next week.

52:35.989 --> 52:39.076
- Next week you'll be in ninth grade.
- Yeah, high school.

52:39.201 --> 52:40.327
Oh, yeah.

52:40.494 --> 52:45.207
You aren't gonna wanna hang round with
a bunch of dumb elementary-school kids.

52:45.457 --> 52:48.961
That's not true. I'll come
and visit you guys all the time.

52:49.211 --> 52:51.255
Yeah, to see your girlfriend.

52:51.421 --> 52:53.298
(boys ) Whooo!

52:54.758 --> 52:56.552
(cackling )

52:56.718 --> 53:00.389
Have some more Sloppy Joes.

53:01.765 --> 53:05.018
I made 'em extra sloppy for yous.

53:07.813 --> 53:11.483
I know how yous kids like 'em sloppy.

53:12.609 --> 53:15.028
Lady, you're scarin' us.

53:41.346 --> 53:46.059
- Do you know where the bathroom is?
- Second door on the left.

53:49.688 --> 53:53.400
Hey, tubby, how about
a little bathroom reading?

53:53.567 --> 53:57.196
I have the August 1983 issue
of Wrestling World here.

53:58.447 --> 54:02.659
There's a terrific article about
a wrestler named the Revolting Blob.

54:04.411 --> 54:08.540
Gee, you know somethin'?
He kinda looks like someone I know.

54:09.750 --> 54:12.669
- Where'd you get that?
- I have a subscription.

54:12.836 --> 54:18.425
Bad guy. He threw one opponent out of
the ring and hit a bunch of senior citizens.

54:20.052 --> 54:22.971
Boy, this wacko looks familiar.

54:23.096 --> 54:26.767
What do I care about some
stupid phoney wrestling guy?

54:26.934 --> 54:28.894
My God.

54:29.019 --> 54:33.816
In June 1983 he sat on
some guy's head and killed him.

54:33.982 --> 54:36.109
It was just a stunt!

54:36.276 --> 54:39.655
He was supposed to pinch my leg
if he was running short of air.

54:39.822 --> 54:44.451
With this guy sitting on everyone's head,
I wonder how he got his teaching degree?

54:44.618 --> 54:46.328
No!

54:46.453 --> 54:50.499
No, you can't do that to me.
Those kids are my whole life!

54:50.666 --> 54:55.504
So you wouldn't want anything to happen
that would make 'em think less of you?

54:55.671 --> 54:57.297
Max?

54:58.257 --> 55:00.092
Max?

55:00.259 --> 55:02.427
You ready to cooperate with me?

55:02.594 --> 55:04.471
Yes.

55:04.638 --> 55:07.307
Then Madison Hotels is as good as mine!

55:19.695 --> 55:21.697
(rock music from car )

55:43.719 --> 55:46.138
(laughter )

55:47.931 --> 55:50.100
- (student ) Nice shirt.
- Yeah. Yep.

55:50.267 --> 55:52.269
(bell rings )

55:57.858 --> 56:03.489
Now the cell's happy. But other molecules
are saying ''We'd like some energy too.''

56:03.655 --> 56:09.620
And it uses its own pigment molecule,
chlorophyll, to carry out the action.

56:09.786 --> 56:13.081
This does not make the ribosomes happy.

56:14.374 --> 56:17.252
And poor chlorophyll is caught
in the middle of this.

56:17.419 --> 56:21.006
Chlorophyll? More like ''bore-ophyll''!

56:22.466 --> 56:24.468
Right?

56:27.095 --> 56:31.517
- Jeez, a little bit stuffy in here, huh?
- Don't talk to me.

56:31.683 --> 56:34.353
- And why is that?
- Because you're a loser.

56:34.520 --> 56:38.649
(teacher ) ..from these ribosomes.
And chlorophyll helps the chloroplast...

56:38.774 --> 56:41.068
No, I will not make out with you!

56:42.110 --> 56:45.781
Did you hear that? This girl wants to
make out with me in the middle of class!

56:45.948 --> 56:49.034
You got ''chlorophyll man'' up there
talkin' about God knows what.

56:49.201 --> 56:54.248
All she's talking about is makin' out with
me. I'm here to learn, not to make out.

56:54.414 --> 56:56.625
Go on with the chlorophyll.

57:01.129 --> 57:03.131
O'Doyle rules.

57:03.882 --> 57:06.718
Thanks a lot, O'Doyle. Nice meetin' you.

57:07.761 --> 57:09.763
(giggling )

57:11.265 --> 57:14.142
- Wait till they start with the wedgies.
- Yeah.

57:14.309 --> 57:18.522
You oughta start cutting your underwear
before you get to school. So it rips easier.

57:18.647 --> 57:20.691
I see. Who are you guys?

57:20.858 --> 57:23.777
The guys everybody used to pick on
before you started here.

57:23.944 --> 57:28.782
No, they ain't pickin' on me. They're givin'
me a hard time cos I'm the new guy.

57:28.949 --> 57:30.868
A little first-day hazing.

57:31.034 --> 57:35.664
- Are you in loser denial or something?
- I had a bad case of loser denial myself.

57:35.831 --> 57:38.792
Till the lacrosse team stuck
a parking cone up my ass.

57:39.293 --> 57:43.338
Loser? I ain't no loser.
I was the king of this high school.

57:43.463 --> 57:46.758
A hundred friends, a million parties...

57:46.925 --> 57:49.219
You guys are losers, not me.

57:51.388 --> 57:54.266
And that is what a prime number is.

57:54.433 --> 57:56.602
(children ) Billy!

57:56.768 --> 58:00.063
I figured I got fourth period off,
I'd shoot down and say hi.

58:00.189 --> 58:03.066
- How's high school, Billy?
- Yeah, how's high school?

58:03.192 --> 58:07.196
High school is great.
I mean, I'm learning a lot.

58:07.321 --> 58:11.867
And all the kids are treating me
very nice. It's great.

58:12.034 --> 58:15.037
Gee, I can't wait till I go to high school.

58:16.497 --> 58:18.749
Don't you say that.

58:18.874 --> 58:21.627
Don't you ever say that.

58:21.752 --> 58:23.879
Stay here.

58:24.004 --> 58:26.965
Stay as long as you can.

58:27.090 --> 58:30.469
For the love of God, cherish it.

58:30.594 --> 58:33.096
(Veronica ) Jennifer,
why don't you read out loud?

58:33.222 --> 58:35.974
You gotta cherish it.

58:36.099 --> 58:38.185
You do.

58:38.310 --> 58:39.937
Hm.

58:44.066 --> 58:45.984
I don't understand it.

58:46.109 --> 58:50.364
I mean, ten years ago high school
was the greatest. I had so much fun.

58:50.489 --> 58:53.492
I guess a little too much fun,
since you've gotta do it again.

58:53.617 --> 58:59.331
I know. It's just that classes are so hard,
and all the kids treat me like I'm a goof.

59:00.123 --> 59:02.417
Well, you are a goof.

59:02.543 --> 59:06.004
Suck it up. Eight more weeks
and you're all set.

59:06.129 --> 59:08.799
Yeah, you're right. You're so smart.

59:11.844 --> 59:13.887
- I gotta go, OK?
- OK.

59:14.805 --> 59:16.431
Billy, wait.

59:17.182 --> 59:20.269
It doesn't feel so great
to be called a loser, does it?

59:20.602 --> 59:21.478
No.

59:21.603 --> 59:24.148
Maybe the first time
you went to high school,...

59:24.273 --> 59:28.902
..you weren't as nice to the kids
that you thought were losers.

59:29.027 --> 59:32.322
I know what you're sayin'.
You're so smart.

59:42.332 --> 59:44.376
(phone rings )

59:47.254 --> 59:48.255
Hello?

59:48.463 --> 59:51.633
- Hi. Is this Danny McGrath?
- Yeah.

59:51.758 --> 59:55.262
The Danny McGrath that graduated
from Knibb High School in 1984?

59:55.971 --> 1:00:00.267
- Uh, yeah. Who's this?
- This is Billy Madison.

1:00:00.392 --> 1:00:04.605
You probably don't remember me,
but I went to high school with you.

1:00:04.730 --> 1:00:07.232
I kinda gave you a hard time back then,...

1:00:07.357 --> 1:00:11.069
..and I did some things that
I thought were funny at the time,...

1:00:11.195 --> 1:00:14.573
..but now I realise they
were just mean and stupid.

1:00:14.698 --> 1:00:18.327
And I just wanted to apologise,
and I hope you forgive me.

1:00:19.119 --> 1:00:21.288
Yeah, sure. Don't worry about it.

1:00:21.872 --> 1:00:24.583
Wow! That's great!

1:00:24.708 --> 1:00:27.794
Well, I am sorry, and maybe
we can get together some time...

1:00:27.920 --> 1:00:29.963
..and have coffee or somethin'.

1:00:30.547 --> 1:00:33.884
- Sure, I'd like that.
- OK. Well, I'll see you around.

1:00:34.009 --> 1:00:36.053
OK. Bye.

1:00:36.178 --> 1:00:40.098
(~ 'Telephone Line'
by Electric Light Orchestra )

1:01:12.506 --> 1:01:14.508
Speak for yourself, moron.

1:01:16.093 --> 1:01:18.595
Oh, my God! That is funny!

1:01:18.720 --> 1:01:23.767
Next.: the shocking story of power
and corruption involving a hotel tycoon.

1:01:23.892 --> 1:01:28.897
How his 27-year-old millionaire son
cheated his way through school.

1:01:29.022 --> 1:01:32.734
- What the hell...?
- Now, now. Maybe it's somebody else.

1:01:34.778 --> 1:01:36.822
My name is Max Anderson,...

1:01:36.947 --> 1:01:42.536
..and I am the principal
at the Polly Fector Elementary School.

1:01:42.661 --> 1:01:46.623
Recently a young man named
Billy Madison was enrolled there.

1:01:46.748 --> 1:01:50.335
During that time
Mr Madison was disruptive.

1:01:50.460 --> 1:01:55.382
The only reason he passed was that
he offered me a bribe of $5,000,...

1:01:55.507 --> 1:01:58.051
.. which I regrettably accepted.

1:01:59.094 --> 1:02:00.554
I'm sorry, Billy.

1:02:00.679 --> 1:02:05.309
(reporter ) That was Principal Anderson
of Polly Fector Elementary School.

1:02:05.434 --> 1:02:07.728
Dad! He's lyin'!

1:02:08.896 --> 1:02:12.524
You made a fool out of me.
This was a mistake from the beginning.

1:02:12.649 --> 1:02:15.944
Brian, I got some interim
forecasts for you to...

1:02:17.279 --> 1:02:20.365
- Why is everybody so glum?
- You seriously don't believe me?

1:02:20.491 --> 1:02:24.328
That's right. I seriously don't believe you.

1:02:24.453 --> 1:02:27.331
The deal's off. Eric's got the company.

1:02:29.500 --> 1:02:32.169
Wow. Good news for me.

1:02:38.425 --> 1:02:41.512
I can't believe this is happening right now.

1:02:44.097 --> 1:02:46.683
Are you gonna come to class on Monday?

1:02:46.809 --> 1:02:49.603
Wouldn't make much sense now, would it?

1:02:50.896 --> 1:02:53.565
Stupid idea in the first place.

1:02:54.566 --> 1:02:57.027
(~ 'Renegade' by Styx )

1:02:57.319 --> 1:02:59.488
~ They finally found me

1:02:59.613 --> 1:03:01.573
~ The renegade who had it made

1:03:01.698 --> 1:03:04.451
~ Retrieved for a bounty

1:03:04.576 --> 1:03:06.745
~ Never more to go astray

1:03:06.870 --> 1:03:10.833
~ This'll be the end today
of the wanted man

1:03:13.377 --> 1:03:15.462
Better get up outta this bed!

1:03:15.587 --> 1:03:20.843
~ I've been years on the lam
And had a high price on my head

1:03:22.970 --> 1:03:26.181
~ Lawman said 'Get him dead or alive'...

1:03:26.306 --> 1:03:28.350
(Billy howling )

1:03:34.064 --> 1:03:36.108
Yoo-hoo!

1:03:37.276 --> 1:03:38.819
Hello!

1:03:38.944 --> 1:03:40.988
Billy's here!

1:03:42.489 --> 1:03:44.491
Hey, baby!

1:03:45.033 --> 1:03:47.202
You lookin' hot tonight!

1:03:47.327 --> 1:03:51.290
- Billy, what has happened to you?
- We're gonna go on a date.

1:03:51.415 --> 1:03:54.710
You, me, Jack and Frank...

1:03:54.835 --> 1:03:59.423
..are gonna go around puttin' shit
on people's doorsteps...

1:03:59.548 --> 1:04:02.259
..and we're gonna set it on fire.

